<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFEFFFCEA5CDFA0B1F74F928" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEFFFCEA5CDFA0B1DB0FA2C" blockId="31.[136,911,1490,1517]" box="[136,911,1490,1517]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFEFFFCEA5CDFA0B1DB0FA2C" box="[136,911,1490,1517]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" reason="4">
10.5. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEFFFCEA582FA0B1CDCFA2D" authority="Schauer (1847: 563)" authorityName="Schauer" authorityPageNumber="563" authorityYear="1847" box="[199,739,1490,1517]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schottiana">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA582FA0B1FCBFA2D" bold="true" box="[199,500,1490,1517]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Stachytarpheta schottiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA4BEFA0B1CDCFA2D" author="Schauer, J. C." box="[507,739,1490,1517]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="522 - 700" refId="ref38872" refString="Schauer, J. C. (1847) Verbenaceae. In: De Candolle, A. P. (Ed.) Prodromus Systematis Naturalis Regni Vegetabilis 11. Sumptibus Sociorum Treuttel et Wu ¨ rtz, Paris, pp. 522 - 700." type="book chapter" year="1847">Schauer (1847: 563)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. (Figs. 3B, 7G)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEFFFCEA5CDF9C31F74F928" blockId="31.[136,1452,1562,2093]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Herbs 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA594F9C31F12F9F5" box="[209,301,1562,1589]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="m" value="0.75" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5‒1 m</quantity>
high, branches tetragonal, not winged, glabrous to puberulous. Leaves opposite, petiole 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA041F9C21B19F9F4" box="[1284,1318,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">ca.</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA069F9C31B52F9F5" box="[1324,1389,1562,1589]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long, blade 1.5‒4.4 × 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA406F9E71FFAF999" box="[323,453,1598,1625]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="15.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="cm" value="0.95" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4‒1.5 cm</quantity>
, chartaceous, elliptical, apex acute to obtuse, base attenuate, decurrent, margin near the base, crenate-serrate toward the apex, glabrous in both surfaces. Inflorescences 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA153F9BB1AB1F9BD" box="[1046,1166,1634,1661]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6149999999999998" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="0.83" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="cm" value="16.15" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="8.3">8.3‒24 cm</quantity>
long, lax; bracts 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA012F9BB1E8BF961" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.85" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="3.85" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="3.2">3.2‒4.5 mm</quantity>
long, lanceolate, abaxial surface glabrous, margin ciliate; calyx 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA6CAF95F1A3DF961" box="[911,1026,1670,1697]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.75" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="7.75" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.5">6.5‒9 mm</quantity>
long, immersed in the depressions of the rachis, 4-toothed, 1 sinus adaxial, glabrous; corolla 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA7B9F9731D5AF905" box="[764,869,1706,1733]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="cm" value="0.9" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.8">0.8‒1 cm</quantity>
long, lilac. Fruit 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA16EF9721A72F904" box="[1067,1101,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">ca.</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA110F9731AA8F905" box="[1109,1175,1706,1733]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long, surrounded by the persistente calyx.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFEFFFF1A5F8F92B1C36FD85" lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEFFFCEA5F8F92B1F26F894" blockId="31.[136,1452,1562,2093]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA5F8F92B1C33F8CC" bold="true" box="[189,524,1778,1804]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEFFFCEA749F92B1D0AF8CC" authorityName="Schauer" authorityYear="1847" box="[524,821,1778,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schottiana">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA749F92B1D0AF8CC" box="[524,821,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Stachytarpheta schottiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA157F92A1A47F8CC" box="[1042,1144,1779,1804]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">restingas</emphasis>
of the 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEFFFCEA195F92B1B46F8CC" box="[1232,1401,1778,1804]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEFFFCEA5CDF8CF1F19F8F0" box="[136,294,1814,1840]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA476F8CF1C54F8F0" author="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G." box="[307,619,1814,1840]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref33512" refString="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G. (2020 c) Stachytarpheta in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 15189 (accessed 4 January 2021)" type="url" year="2020">Cardoso &amp; Salimena 2020c</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEFFFCEA7DCF8CF1D04F8F0" box="[665,827,1814,1840]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, it was recorded in only one SPA: Parque Estadual Paulo 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEFFFCEA5CDF8E31EF7F894" box="[136,200,1850,1876]" country="Colombia" name="Cesar" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">César</collectingRegion>
Vinha.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEFFFCEA5F8F8871F3EF85C" blockId="31.[136,1452,1562,2093]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA5F8F8871F60F8B8" bold="true" box="[189,351,1886,1912]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Collected with flowers and fruits in February, March, April, July, September, November, and December.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFEFFFF1A5F8F87F1D1BFEC1" blockId="31.[136,1452,1562,2093]" lastBlockId="32.[136,1452,158,581]" lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA5F8F87F1C41F800" bold="true" box="[189,638,1958,1984]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Preliminary conservation assessment:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEFFFCEA7DCF87F1D81F800" authorityName="Schauer" authorityYear="1847" box="[665,958,1958,1984]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schottiana">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA7DCF87F1D81F800" box="[665,958,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Stachytarpheta schottiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rare species, found in small populations, with few records in scientific collections (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA71DF8131D7CF824" author="Salimena, F. R. G. &amp; Kutschenko, D. C. &amp; Monteiro, N. P. &amp; Mynssen, C." box="[600,835,1994,2020]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1010 - 1016" refId="ref38365" refString="Salimena, F. R. G., Kutschenko, D. C., Monteiro, N. P. &amp; Mynssen, C. (2013) Verbenaceae. In: Martinelli, G. &amp; Moraes, M. A. (Eds.) Livro vermelho da flora do Brasil. CNCFlora, Rio de Janeiro, pp. 1010 - 1016." type="book chapter" year="2013">
Salimena 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA78DF8121D3FF824" box="[712,768,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). It has an EOO of approximately 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA1F9F8131B0BF824" box="[1212,1332,1994,2020]" metricMagnitude="7" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.713" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="km" value="17130.0">17,130 km</quantity>
<superScript id="7C259BEBFFEFFFCEA076F8131B04F818" attach="left" box="[1331,1339,1994,2008]" fontSize="6" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">2</superScript>
and AOO of 
<quantity id="4CA89B46FFEFFFCEA5ECF8371ECCF7C8" box="[169,243,2030,2057]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="km" value="52.0">52 km</quantity>
<superScript id="7C259BEBFFEFFFCEA5B6F8371EC4F83C" attach="left" box="[243,251,2030,2044]" fontSize="6" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">2</superScript>
. This species is endemic to the 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA731F8361CE5F7C8" box="[628,730,2031,2056]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">restingas</emphasis>
, a highly threatened environment because of the demographic growing and real estate speculation (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA768F7CB1CFCF7EC" author="Pereira, J. O." box="[557,707,2066,2092]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="27 - 32" refId="ref37377" refString="Pereira, J. O. (2007) Formacoes pioneiras: restingas. In: Simonelli, M. &amp; Fraga, C. N. (Eds.) Especies da flora ameacadas de extincao no estado do Espirito Santo. IPEMA, Vitoria, pp 27 - 32." type="book chapter" year="2007">Pereira 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA795F7CB1D81F7EC" author="Thomazi, R. D. &amp; Rocha, R. T. &amp; Oliveira, M. V. &amp; Bruno, A. S. &amp; Silva, A. G." box="[720,958,2066,2092]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref39633" refString="Thomazi, R. D., Rocha, R. T., Oliveira, M. V., Bruno, A. S. &amp; Silva, A. G. (2013) Um panorama da vegetacao das restingas do Espirito Santo no contexto do litoral Brasileiro. Natureza On line 11: 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2013">
Thomazi 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA678F7CA1D48F7EC" box="[829,887,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEFFFCEA12AF7CB1B35F7EC" author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Committee" box="[1135,1290,2066,2092]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref34955" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Committee (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 30 December 2019)" type="book" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFEFFFCEA05DF7CA1B93F7EC" authorityName="Schauer" authorityYear="1847" box="[1304,1452,2066,2093]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schottiana">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEFFFCEA05DF7CA1B93F7EC" box="[1304,1452,2066,2093]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">S. schottiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be classified as “Endangered” (EN) because of the restricted AOO, number of known locations, and declining habitat quality. However, due to the occurrence inside PAs in 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFD0FFF1A66BFF1B1D4AFF1C" box="[814,885,194,220]" name="Brazil" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, we adopted a more conservative point of view and considered the species “Vulnerable” VU (EN) B2ab(i,ii,iii).
</paragraph>
